	* pylibs/AE/Executables.py (PythonExecutable.run): made so raising
	DTHaltError works within python components

2004-02-16  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/PyDO/PyDO2.py (_pydobase): setting default value of the
	mutable property to be 1, as in the original PyDO.

2004-02-10  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/AE/CacheTag.py (CacheTag.genCode): remove incorrect
	generated code that referred to __h.TimeUtil.

2004-02-05  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/SkunkWeb/Server.py (_aPrefixIn): typo fix that caused 
	errors every request for people using userModuleCleanup

2004-01-20  Brian Olsen  <brian@qinternet.com>

	* pylibs/PyDO/PyDO.py "order" for get...() methods can accept a
	string or tuple of strings and tuples. Each tuple in the tuple must
	contain two values, the column name and "ASC" or "DESC".

	* pylibs/PyDO/PyDO2.py Same feature addition as in PyDO.py.

2004-01-15  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/AE/Cache.py (_mcCompileFunc): fix for Windows line
	returns and message catalogs (as is already done for templates and
	python code).

2004-01-12  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/skunk/date/format.py (HTTPDate): adding (replacing
	equivalent function in Date module).

2004-01-10  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/templating/Handler.py: bug fix: now hide .inc
	and .pyinc files from requests! 

	* pylibs/AE/Cache.py (_genCacheKey): use different cachekey
	function if key files aren't being written.  I think this works,
	but it needs testing.
	

2004-01-05  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib/validates.py (STATELIST): added Arkansas, which
	was missing for some reason, and fixed the state code for Arizona.

2003-12-31  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* configure, configure.in: no longer test for egenix-mx.

	* SkunkWeb/Services/templating/MailServices.py (sendmail),
	SkunkWeb/Services/templating/Handler.py,
	SkunkWeb/Services/web/protocol.py: removed dependencies on Date
	and mx.DateTime.

	* pylibs/skunk/date/timeutil.py (arpa): equivalent of
	mx.DateTime.ARPA.str.

	* pylibs/AE/InitTags.py (initTags): inclusion of DateTag is now
	conditional on the presence of mx (and will remain that way as
	long as DateTag depends on it).
	
2003-12-29  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/AE/CacheTag.py: now use skunk.date.timeutil rather than
	Date.Timeutil

2003-12-27  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/ecs/xhtml.py (parse): now use HTMLParser rather than
	expat, so html entity references are now tolerated (although
	treated as strings).

2003-12-24  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/skunk/__init__.py, pylibs/skunk/date/__init__.py,
	pylibs/skunk/date/timeutil.py: new timeutil module, still rough, 
	with the goal of no longer requiring mx.DateTime; starting "skunk"
	package, with the intention of gradually moving much of pylibs
	into it, to better avoid name collisions and make installation of
	pylibs into python's normal site-packages more workable.

2003-12-18  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/web/protocol.py (_processRequest): added
	ProcessResponse hook for response filtering, as prompted by patch
	from Adam DePrince.

2003-12-11  Jacob Smullyan  <jsmullyan@wnyc.org>

	* SkunkWeb/mod_skunkweb/mod_skunkweb.c (critical_error): apache2
	bugfix: wrong test for return value of apr_file_open().

2003-11-30  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/sessionHandler/SQLSessionStore.py
	(AbstractSQLSessionStore.getConnection): bug fix for the
	postgresql implementation -- attempting to call fetchall on a
	cursor when there are no rows is not tolerated by pypgsql.

2003-11-29  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/mod_skunkweb/mod_skunkweb.c: replace references to AE
	and AED with SkunkWeb.

	* SkunkWeb/Services/sessionHandler/PostgreSQLSessionStore.py:
	several changes so it actually works (previous version did not).

	* SkunkWeb/Services/sessionHandler/SQLSessionStore.py
	(AbstractSQLSessionStore._getPickle): fix for bytea using
	pypgsql. 

2003-11-24  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/PyDO/PyDO2.py (_metapydo.__new__): looping through
	<dict>.iteritems() and mutating the dict can lead to hash
	rearrangement, apparently; patch from Jeroen van Dongen (no longer
	use iteritems, which was pointless anyway).

2003-11-22  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/httpd/protocol.py
	(HTTPProtocol.marshalResponse): bug fix that permits httpd to send
	multiple headers with the same name (as in Set-Cookie).  Thanks to
	Dan Chow for reporting this.

2003-11-17  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/product/loader.py (Product.__reallyload): when
	using Python 2.3 or better, using zipimport if the product is a 
	zip file.

2003-10-20 Brian Olsen <brian@qinternet.com>

	* pylibs/PyDO/PyDO.py: Added "order", "limit", and "offset"
	parameters to getSome(), getSomeSQL(), getTupleWhere() and
	getSQLWhere(); they are used to use the respective SQL 
	commands "ORDER BY", "LIMIT" and "OFFSET."

	* pylibs/PyDO/PyDO2.py: Added "order", "limit" and "offset"
	here; it is the same functionality as in PyDO.py.

2003-09-15  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/PyDO/PyDO2.py: Jeroen van Dongen's revision of PyDO2, 
	slightly revised by me (I re-added useAttrs, also took out
	the string module for no particular reason). 

2003-09-07  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/httpd/protocol.py
	(HTTPMethodRequestParser._getEnv): now unquote the path.

	* SkunkWeb/Services/web/__init__.py (__initHooks): added http 
	logging function to PostRequest hook.

	* SkunkWeb/Services/templating/Handler.py (requestHandler):
	commenting out debug statements inside for loop.

	* SkunkWeb/sw.conf.in: fix for logfile paths, and added http
	access log.

	* SkunkWeb/Services/web/protocol.py (HTTPConnection.__init__):
	added a "_rawOutput" attribute to CONNECTION, to support http
	logging; (_accesslog): added hook function for CLF http access
	logging, based on patch by Jeroen van Dongen. 

	* SkunkWeb/SkunkWeb/confvars.py.in (DEFAULT_HTTP_ACCESS_LOG),
	SkunkWeb/SkunkWeb/LogObj.py: support for separate http access log.

	* pylibs/Logger.py (HTTP_ACCESS): CLF HTTP access logging, based
	on a patch from Jeroen van Dongen.

2003-08-27  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* docs/manual/instConfig.txt: some little changes.

2003-08-23  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/swmgr.in: typo-type bug fix.

	* pylibs/Date/Format.py (_DateFormatter.format): stop passing 
	the mx.DateTime tuple() to time.strftime, as it causes a
	DeprecationWarning with Python 2.3 (until Lemburg fixes it, at
	least) and is pointless anyway.

