	* SkunkWeb/Services/sessionHandler/Session.py (Session.setDirty): 
	restoring mutator method that I had inadvertently removed.

2003-08-16  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/web/protocol.py (_processRequest): no longer
	call CONNECTION.response() twice (is returned from
	HandleConnection).  Caught by Jeroen van Dongen.

2003-08-15  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/sessionHandler/Session.py (getSession):
	default value of create option changed from 0 to 1.

2003-08-13  Jacob Smullyan  <jsmullyan@wnyc.org>

	* util/rpm/skunkweb.spec: removed cachefile argument from cronjob
	invocation of cache reaper.

2003-08-12  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* due to breakage of product service, cutting a 3.4b5 release.

	* pylibs/AE/Cache.py (_fixPath): now applying normpath twice.
	This prevents the the docroot from being escaped, but also
	normalizes the entire path (removing extra slashes).  Otherwise,
	the vfs breaks in some cases (most notably with the product service).

2003-08-11  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* new beta (3.4b4) release cut, to get the security fixes out
	there asap (it was about time anyway).

	* pylibs/AE/Cache.py (_fixPath): now impossible once again to
	escape the docroot.  Thanks for finding this bug (and fix), Jeroen!

	* SkunkWeb/Services/templating/Handler.py (fourOhFourHandler): fix
	for cross-site scripting vulnerability in default 404 page,
	reported by Jeroen van Dongen.

2003-08-11 Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/util/cache_reaper.py.in: now a swpython script,
	and by default finds all the scoped component cache roots and clears them. 

