	* pylibs/vfs/importer.py (ExtInPkgImporter.getmod): some
	impossible code fixed; it got called on one machine and not
	another, for mysterious reasons.

2003-02-17  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/SocketMan/SocketMan.py (SocketMan.addConnection): code
	to delete unix socket files if they are hanging around where we
	expect to create them; other files don't get deleted.

	* SkunkWeb/Services/httpd/protocol.py
	(HTTPMethodRequestParser._getEnv):  permit httpd service to be run
	on a UNIX socket, as requested by Remi Delon. 

2003-02-11  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/argextract.py (extract_args): fix for default values.

2003-02-11 Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/vfs/importer.py (VFSOwner.getmod): Package imports were
	broken, but now they seem to work.

2003-02-08  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/sessionHandler/FSSessionStore.py
	(FSSessionStoreImpl.__setPickle): wrapping calls to the pickler in
	try/except so the pickle files will be unlocked even in the case
	of error.

2003-02-08 Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/product/loader.py (get_product_path): added
	useful little function.

2003-02-08  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/xmlrpchandler.py: fix for methodSignature, whose purpose
	had been misunderstood.  The original implementation, which
	returned the *call* signature of the underlying Python method, 
	is retained as system.methodPydoc.

2003-02-07 Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/vfs/rosio.py (RO_StringIO.__iter__): removed xreadlines, since
	it produces a DeprecationWarning with Python 2.3a1.

2003-02-07 Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/templating/UrlBuilder.py: now XHTML-compliant
	by default.  

	* pylibs/PyDO/mysqlconn.py (PyDOMySQL.sqlStringAndValue): fix for NULL.

	* pylibs/setup-pylibs.in: distutils setup script used by the
	Makefile to build extension modules.

	* pylibs/Makefile.in: now uses distutils to build the extension modules;
	excludes some deprecated or unnecessary material from being built
	and installed.  Now works with Python 2.3a1!

	* Makefile.in: SW_VERSION is now defined here.


2003-02-06 Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/PyDO/mysqlconn.py (PyDOMySQL.__unpackConnectArgs): 
	allow verbosity to be specified in a connectstring.
	(PyDOMySQL.getAutoIncrement): fix for autoincrement.

2003-02-05 Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/rewrite.py: made it possible to pass
	a callable to RewriteCond for string keyword arguments (this was
	already permitted for integer kwargs), and added some
	documentation taken from the Open Source Digest article.


2003-02-02  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/sample_webdocs/index.html: cleaned up slightly.

	* SkunkWeb/configure.in: dropping --with-services configure
	option, which is pointless.
	
	* SkunkWeb/swpython.py.in: now set version correctly.
	
	* starting to prepare release 3.4b1.  I'm going to prepare
	the release a little differently to produce a cleaner tarball.

2003-01-29  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/rewrite.py: Pretty thorough overhaul:  
   	  - The hooks are now disabled by default, although they can be turned on 
	    by setting Configuration.rewriteEnableHooks to a true value.
	  - Yesterday's HostMatchBase stuff is gone; instead, added a
	    RewriteCond for doing scope-like things, and altered the rewrite
	    rule processing loop.  
	  - DynamicRewriter is no longer callable; it has a rewrite method,
	    and the rewrite loop doesn't do a type check, but looks for a
	    method by that name.  The method doesn't return anything; it is
	    passed the connection and does anything it wants to it.  Also, 
	    DynamicRewriters no longer get the  behavior of having
            match.groupdict() merged into CONNECTION.args.

2003-01-28  Jacob Smullyan  <jsmullyan@wnyc.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/rewrite.py (ExtraPathFinder.__call__): jeez,
	this was called "call" rather than "__call__".  Obviously in much
	use. 
	(_HostMatchBase): added host-specific rewriters.

2003-01-22  Jacob Smullyan  <jsmullyan@wnyc.org>

	* pylibs/argextract.py: fixing import error.

2003-01-21  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib: many changes, back and forth, resulting
	in no detectable forward progress.

2003-01-13  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/AE/Cache.py (_writeCompileCache): fixed typo.

2003-01-12  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/PyPgSQLcache.py: the pylibs used by the driver, below.

	* SkunkWeb/Services/pypgsqlcache.py: caching service for pypgsql
	driver.  This design is a pain in the neck.

	* pylibs/PyDO/pypgsqlconn.py: first draft of pypgsql PyDO driver,
	submitted by "John Pydo".

2003-01-11  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/PostgreSql/__init__.py: whitespace normalization; removed
	some dead code.

2003-01-10  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib/dispatcher.py (Goto, Push, Pop): added optional
	"args" argument to constructors.

2003-01-06  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* test/formlib/htdocs: numerous revisions to work with the
	refactoring of formlib.

	* pylibs/formlib: considerable refactoring to dispatcher, forms,
	and views.  The upshot of it all being that the dispatcher is now
	abstract; it doesn't assume that the dispatcher needs to start out
	with a reference to all the form objects.  Similarly, the form's
	process() method doesn't make assumptions about what is passed to
	it. Also, fields have a _setData(dict) method now, so we don't
	need to test (in Form.setData()) for field type; and in views.py,
	I removed the isviewable() method, and instead test for the
	presence of the "getView" method.

2003-01-03  James Richards  <jrichards@satie.wnyc.org>

	* test/formlib/htdocs/testAllViews.pyinc (form): Adding
	multipart/form-data enctype and display of uploaded file
	characteristics

2003-01-02  James Richards  <jrichards@satie.wnyc.org>

	* test/formlib/htdocs/testDispatch2.pyinc: modified test to work
	with current formlib definition, note that testDispatch3 is also
	misbehaving

