2002-11-21  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib/form.py (_getname): change to make the form
	pickleable. 

	* pylibs/formlib/state.py: change to make
	the state pickleable, which is rather crucial.

	* pylibs/containers/fieldcontainer.py (_donothing): made the
	FieldContainer pickleable by moving the default value of
	fieldmapper from a lambda to a top-level function, and by adding
	__getstate__ and __setstate__ methods (since I'm using
	__slots__). 

2002-11-20  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib/state.py: made stateEncoder => stateEncryptor.

	* pylibs/aesencrypt.py: moved aesencode.py to aesencrypt.py and
	renamed encode/decode to encrypt/decrypt, so as not to wince every
	time I see the module.  Also, now rotors objects have the same
	interface, which is helpful to formlib.state.InPageStateManager.

2002-11-20  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib/state.py (InPageStateManager.setstate): moved
	AESEncoder to the aesencode module.

	* pylibs/aesencode.py: adding a simple wrapper around
	PyCrypto.Cipher.AES that means you don't have to worry about the
	block-size or the length of what you want to encode.
	
2002-11-19  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib/state.py: some cleanup; not ready yet.

	* test/formlib/htdocs/test3.html: another test.

	* pylibs/formlib/form.py (Form.validate): errors are now kept as
	part of the form's state.  (Form.submit): to submit a form, you
	now call "submit(data)"; it resets and validates for you.

2002-11-18  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* test/formlib/htdocs/test2.html: second simple test created and
	passed (simple select field and button group).

	* pylibs/formlib/form.py (Field.checkValue,
	DomainField.checkValue): among several other changes made in
	debugging, this changes the interface.  checkValue now returns the
	value and performs some munging to permit 'multiple' fields to
	absorb single values.

	* pylibs/formlib/views.py: fixed many bugs, mostly out-of-order
	arguments to constructors (now I know why they are called args --
	AAARGH!).

	* test/formlib/htdocs/: created first *very* simple test.

	* pylibs/formlib/views.py (ViewableForm.getView): show
	descriptions.

	* pylibs/containers/fieldcontainer.py
	(FieldContainer.__setitem__): fixed typo.

	* pylibs/containers/set.py: adding brain-dead set implementation
	(luckily sets will be part of Python 2.3).

	* pylibs/formlib/views.py, pylibs/formlib/form.py: now reached a
	point where it is possible to test it with simple forms.  Added
	description field to all fields.

2002-11-14  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/formlib/form.py: the field classes are now somewhat
	reasonable; Form isn't there yet.

2002-11-13  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/web/protocol.py (HTTPConnection.extract_args):
	now use argextract.

	* pylibs/formlib/form.py: start of clean-up, using
	fieldcontainer.py. 

	* pylibs/containers/fieldcontainer.py (FieldContainer): added
	a "storelists" property.

	* pylibs/containers/__init__.py: created a package for containers,
	in anticipation of eventually needing to write more of them.

	* pylibs/containers/fieldcontainer.py: adding a hybrid list/dict
	container that I needed for formlib.

2002-11-12  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* docs/tutorial/src: (many files) various changes, still very rough
	and incomplete.

	* pylibs/argextract.py: Since this code looks like it might get used
	outside of CONNECTION, I'm moving it to its own module.

2002-11-10  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/rewrite.py: Moved rewrite hook by default to
	HaveConnection, which occurs before scoping takes place. Added
	Configuration variable, rewriteBeforeScope, to control this (if it
	has a false value, rewrite will take place in PreHandleConnection,
	as before, but it defaults to 1).  I can see arguments for both
	places, but in my case I found it troubling that auth and rewrite
	were using the same hook, although I wasn't actually see bugs
	result from it.

	* docs/tutorial/src/htdocs/games/game.comp: It is now possible to 
	add text to a story.

2002-11-08  Jacob Smullyan  <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* pylibs/AE/Cache.py (getMessageCatalog): a fix for relative paths
	in getting message catalogs that Drew had posted to the list in
	August but not checked in (probably was waiting for someone on the
	list to say it worked).

	* pylibs/ecs/xhtml.py (EMPTY_ELEMENTS): For some reason, I had "i"
	here where I clearly had begun to type "input".  Oops.

2002-11-07  Jacob Smullyan <smulloni@smullyan.org>

	* SkunkWeb/Services/auth/__init__.py (CookieAuthBase.logout): fix
	to prevent two cookies from being created with the same name and
	different paths.

	* docs/tutoria/src/htdocs/: (various files) more files added.

