	* pylibs/PyDO/sqliteconn.py (PyDOSqlite.getAutoIncrement): I
	forgot that the CVS version of pysqlite exposed the function that
	returns the last insert rowid; now am using it and solved my
	auto-increment problem.

	* pylibs/static.py (Sissubclass): patch (from Drew) so that it
	returns 0 rather than inappropriately raising an exception.

	* pylibs/PyDO/sqliteconn.py (test): fixes, now that I have patched
	pysqlite to deal correctly with rowcount.  The way I have
	auto_increment working here isn't very pleasing, however.

